        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: restrict destructive tools during heartbeat sessions (#88843)",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThis PR addresses issue #88843 where agents would hallucinate user requests during autonomous heartbeat polls and create fabricated content.\n\n## Changes\n\n1.  **Tool Restrictions:** Modified `src/agents/agent-tools.ts` to explicitly deny `write`, `exec`, `edit`, `bash`, and `apply_patch` tools when the session trigger is `heartbeat`. This prevents the agent from making permanent changes during a background poll.\n2.  **Prompt Hardening:** Updated `src/agents/system-prompt.ts` to include strict instructions for heartbeat sessions, emphasizing that the agent must NOT hallucinate work or invent requests.\n\n## Verification\n\nVerified that the `trigger === 'heartbeat'` logic correctly injects the `deny` policy into the tool pipeline.",
